			=09
			=09
					<div class=3D"entry-content">
					<p><iframe id=3D"idIframe" style=3D"max-width: 98%; height: 1400px; wi=
dth: 100%; border: none; overflow: hidden;" src=3D"cid:frame-6384E1147BD793=
732EE992EA3CC22C68@mhtml.blink"><span style=3D"display: inline-block; width=
: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" data-mce-type=3D"bookmark" class=
=3D"mce_SELRES_start"></span></iframe><span style=3D"font-size: 8pt; color:=
 #c8c8c7;">Dijkstra=E2=80=99s Shortest Path Algorithm is a technique for fi=
nding the shortest route between a starting point and other points in a gra=
ph with weighted edges. It progressively updates distances from the start b=
y exploring neighboring nodes, leading to an optimal path when all nodes ar=
e considered. It=E2=80=99s effective for non-negative weights, used in navi=
gation and networking, but not for graphs with negative weights or numerous=
 edges.</span></p>
<p><a href=3D"https://p-library.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Dijkstra-_re=
size.jpg"><img fetchpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" class=3D"wp-image-=
241753 size-medium alignleft" src=3D"https://p-library.com/wp-content/uploa=
ds/2023/08/Dijkstra-_resize-300x224.jpg" alt=3D"" width=3D"300" height=3D"2=
24"></a></p>
					</div>

			=09
				</article>

		=09

